"We are pleased with our third quarter organizational results," said Jon Rousseau, Chairman, President, and Chief Executive Officer of the Company. "The performance in the quarter and ongoing progress throughout the year have been underpinned by our ability to deliver high-quality, patient-centric, and lower-cost care across the Pharmacy and Provider segments. We continue to focus on driving best practices in operations while leveraging our scale to provide quality and efficient services to complex populations in a timely, coordinated, and compassionate manner. We remain focused on executing at a high level towards BrightSpring's goals for the remainder of 2025 and into 2026."

Increased 2025 Revenue guidance and reiterated Adjusted EBITDA guidance, which excludes the Community Living business and the effects of any future closed acquisitions. All growth rates are shown as compared to the full year 2024 Revenue and Adjusted EBITDA results, excluding the Community Living business:

Leverage was 3.31x, as calculated under our First Lien Credit Agreement at September 30, 2025. The results of the Community Living business are included in such calculation pursuant to our First Lien Credit Agreement.

Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co, L.P. and certain members of management, offered for sale in a secondary offering an aggregate of 15,000,000 shares of common stock of BrightSpring, of which BrightSpring repurchased 1,500,000 shares. Both the offering and share repurchase closed on October 22, 2025.

Planned divestiture of Community Living business to Sevita, announced on January 20, 2025, is expected to close in Q1 2026.

Adjusted EBITDA 1 of $160 million, up 37.2% compared to $117 million in the third quarter of 2024.

Third quarter net income of $37.5 million, compared to net loss of $25.7 million in the third quarter of 2024.

Gross Profit of $392 million, up 21.3% compared to $323 million in the third quarter of 2024.

Revenues of $3,334 million, up 28.2% compared to $2,601 million in the third quarter of 2024.

